<br>
Translocate has been selling for ungodly high prices, at least on my server (Veeshan).<br>
<br>
Earlier this week, I saw what HAS to be a new record. This spell sold for 60k pp in NFP.  Yup - you read that right 60,000 platinum.  Sixty Thousand.  And it SOLD at that price.  Did a /who on the guy selling it.... guess what? A warrior.<br>
<br>
Does this sorta piss anyone else off? Why in the WORLD is this spell so darned expensive?  It certainly doesn't have any immediate benefit to us.  We can gate to OUR bind point, remember?  It benefits that profiteering tank who sold it for 60k, yet he still felt obliged to gouge the wizard.  That's like charging  a cleric 60k pp for a peridot when you want a symbol from him and he has no reagent.  I sure hope that sucker wiz who bought it turned around and charged that tank 60k pp to TL him.<br>
<br>
Are we THAT desperate to feel &quot;needed&quot; in a group that we will fork over that kind of cash for a spell that only benefits others?  Come on guys, we should stop being chumps and paying so much for this spell - it's NOT really worth it to US no matter how cool it is.  THEY'RE the ones who need us to have it - not us. They should be giving it to us, or at least charging a more modest fee.  I would even pay maybe 100-200pp for it... but no higher.  That's just extortion.<br>
<br>
/rant off... sorry - seeing that sale just made me mad, and I've been down on EQ enough lately aside from that. <p><hr>
